  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Key elements often include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's source\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the money into the legitimate economy\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most involve intentional efforts to disguise the proceeds of criminal activity.",
